99 Problems ProblemPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/99problems.</p> <pre><code>import math
n = int(input())
ceil = math.ceil(n / 100) * 100 - 1
floor = math.floor(n / 100) * 100 - 1
if ceil == floor:
print(ceil)
else:
if abs(ceil - n) &lt;= abs(n - floor) or floor &lt; 0:
print(ceil)
else:
print(floor)
</code></pre> Aaah! ProblemGoPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/aaah.</p> <pre><code>package main
