print(f"{sum(above_ave)/len(numbers):.3%}")
</code></pre> ACM Contest Scoring ProblemPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/acm.</p> <pre><code>problems = {}
solved = set()
while True:
line = input()
if line == "-1":
break
t, p, ans = line.split()
t = int(t)
if p in solved:
continue
if p not in problems:
problems[p] = [(t, ans)]
else:
problems[p].append((t, ans))
if ans == "right":
solved.add(p)
score = 0
for p in problems:
t, ans = problems[p][-1]
if ans == "right":
score += t + 20 * len(problems[p][:-1])
print(len(solved), score)
</code></pre> Add Two Numbers ProblemGoPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/addtwonumbers.</p> <pre><code>package main
