print(a + b)
</code></pre> Akcija ProblemPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/akcija.</p> <pre><code>n = int(input())
c = [int(input()) for _ in range(n)]
c = sorted(c, reverse=True)
groups = [c[i : i + 3] if i + 3 &lt; n else c[i:] for i in range(0, n, 3)]
print(sum(sum(g if len(g) &lt; 3 else g[:2]) for g in groups))
</code></pre> Alphabet Spam ProblemPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/alphabetspam.</p> <pre><code>s = input()
total = len(s)
whites = s.count("_")
lowers = len([c for c in s if ord(c) &gt;= ord("a") and ord(c) &lt;= ord("z")])
uppers = len([c for c in s if ord(c) &gt;= ord("A") and ord(c) &lt;= ord("Z")])
symbols = total - whites - lowers - uppers
print(f"{whites/total:.15f}")
print(f"{lowers/total:.15f}")
print(f"{uppers/total:.15f}")
print(f"{symbols/total:.15f}")
</code></pre> Amsterdam Distance ProblemPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/amsterdamdistance.</p> <pre><code>import math
m, n, r = input().split()
m = int(m)
n = int(n)
r = float(r)
coords = [int(d) for d in input().split()]
p = r / n
dist1 = 0
dist1 += p * abs(coords[1] - coords[3])
dist1 += (
math.pi
* r
* ((min(coords[3], coords[1]) if coords[3] != coords[1] else coords[1]) / n)
* (abs(coords[0] - coords[2]) / m)
)
dist2 = p * abs(coords[1] + coords[3])
print(min(dist1, dist2))
</code></pre> A New Alphabet ProblemPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/anewalphabet.</p> <pre><code>mapping = {
