if a &lt; b or (a + b) % 2:
print("impossible")
else:
print((a + b) // 2, (a - b) // 2)
</code></pre> Beavergnaw ProblemPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/beavergnaw.</p> <pre><code>import math
while True:
D, V = [int(d) for d in input().split()]
if not D and not V:
break
# R = D / 2
# r = d / 2
# V + π * (r**2) * (2*r) + 2 * (1/3) * π * (R-r) * (r**2 + r*R + R**2) == π * (R**2) * (2*R)
print(math.pow(D**3 - 6 * V / math.pi, 1 / 3))
</code></pre> Bela ProblemPython <p>See detail at https://open.kattis.com/problems/bela.</p> <pre><code>table = {
